# Enforce EZKL Variant Selection For GPU Runs (Infra + Docs)

## Summary
Make EZKL package choice explicit and enforceable via infra scripts, and document that GPU proving/bench runs must be executed inside the dev container.  
Chosen behavior:
- `start-dev.sh` gets `--ezkl-package {ezkl|ezkl-gpu}` with conditional rebuild.
- default remains `ezkl` when flag is omitted.
- `bootstrap-instance.sh` gets matching flag for one-time build consistency.

## Implementation Changes
- Update image metadata for enforcement:
  - Add Docker build label in `infra/docker/Dockerfile`:
    - `LABEL aa.ezkl_pypi_package=$EZKL_PYPI_PACKAGE`
  - Keep existing `ARG EZKL_PYPI_PACKAGE=ezkl`.
- Update `infra/scripts/start-dev.sh`:
  - Add flag parsing: `--ezkl-package ezkl|ezkl-gpu`.
  - Validate value; fail fast on invalid input.
  - Before `docker compose up`:
    - Inspect remote image label `aa.ezkl_pypi_package` for `aa-zklora-dev:latest`.
    - If image missing or label != requested package, run rebuild:
      - `EZKL_PYPI_PACKAGE=<selected> docker compose build dev`
    - If rebuild happened, run `docker compose up -d --force-recreate dev`; otherwise existing `up -d dev`.
  - Keep existing `--jupyter` and `--no-shell` behavior unchanged.
- Update `infra/scripts/bootstrap-instance.sh`:
  - Add optional `--ezkl-package ezkl|ezkl-gpu` (default `ezkl`).
  - Pass build arg during remote build:
    - `docker build --build-arg EZKL_PYPI_PACKAGE=<selected> ...`
- Update `infra/README.md`:
  - Add explicit statement in daily workflow/docs:
    - GPU runs must be done inside the dev container.
    - Host shell is not the execution target for benchmark/prover runs.
  - Document new script usage:
    - `./scripts/start-dev.sh --ezkl-package ezkl-gpu`
    - `./scripts/bootstrap-instance.sh --ezkl-package ezkl-gpu`
  - Add verification snippet:
    - image label check and `ezkl.prove` signature check from inside container.
  - Keep all existing cost/security guidance intact.

## Public Interface Changes
- New CLI options:
  - `infra/scripts/start-dev.sh --ezkl-package {ezkl|ezkl-gpu}`
  - `infra/scripts/bootstrap-instance.sh --ezkl-package {ezkl|ezkl-gpu}`
- No changes to app/runtime API surfaces (`mvp_server` endpoints and payloads unchanged).

## Test Plan
- Script behavior validation:
  - `start-dev.sh --ezkl-package ezkl-gpu` on VM with `ezkl` image triggers rebuild.
  - Re-running with same package does not rebuild.
  - Switching back to `--ezkl-package ezkl` triggers rebuild.
  - Invalid package value exits with clear error.
- Bootstrap validation:
  - `bootstrap-instance.sh --ezkl-package ezkl-gpu` passes build arg and completes build.
- Runtime verification checks:
  - `docker image inspect aa-zklora-dev:latest` shows correct `aa.ezkl_pypi_package` label.
  - Inside container: `python3 -c "import inspect, ezkl; print(inspect.signature(ezkl.prove))"` executes successfully.
- Docs validation:
  - `infra/README.md` includes explicit “GPU runs inside container” statement and new command examples.

## Assumptions
- Compose v2 is available on the VM and supports env-invoked build args via command prefix.
- `aa-zklora-dev:latest` remains the canonical image tag.
- `ezkl` remains default package unless `--ezkl-package` is provided.
